15 Act," is amended by revising Code Section 20-2-183, relating to program weights to reflect
16 funds for maintenance and operation of facilities, as follows:
17 "20-2-183.
18 (a) All program weights, when multiplied by the base amount, shall reflect sufficient funds
19 to provide for the maintenance and operation of facilities essential for housing instructional
20 programs and essential supportive educational services, subject to appropriation by the
21 General Assembly.
22 (b)(1) All program weights, when multiplied by the base amount, shall reflect sufficient
23 funds to provide funding assistance to reimburse eligible public schools for actual costs
24 incurred to reduce school violence and improve school safety and security. Such funds
25 may be referred to as school security protection and safety infrastructure funds.
26 (2) The State Board of Education shall annually determine the amount of state funds
27 needed to provide funding assistance to eligible public schools as set forth in paragraph
28 (1) of this subsection, subject to the following conditions:
29 (A) No public school shall be considered eligible for such funding assistance unless
30 such school complies with such policies, procedures, regulations, and other
31 requirements as adopted by the State Board of Education pursuant to paragraph (3) of
32 this subsection; and
33 (B) Expenditures allowable under this subsection shall be limited to:
34 (i) Mobile surveillance camera trailers;
35 (ii) Onsite command centers;
36 (iii) Weapon detection technology for large events, daily campus entry, or any other
37 school function;
38 (iv) Systems designed to detect cigarettes, cigars, consumable vapor products, or
39 alternative nicotine products, as such terms are defined in Code Section 48-11-1; or
40 (v) Systems designed to detect marijuana as such term is defined in Code Section
41 16-13-21.
